     * - Average Case: O(n log n) -  On average, the pivot divides the array reasonably well.
     * - Worst Case: O(n^2) - Occurs when the pivot consistently divides the array into highly unbalanced subarrays (e.g., when the array is already sorted or nearly sorted).
