*   **Time Complexity:** All getter and setter methods: O(1)
*   **Space Complexity:** O(1) - Constant space for member variables.

**ParkingLot Class:**
*   **Time Complexity:**
    *   `parkVehicle()`: O(m*n), where m is the number of floors and n is the number of spots per floor (in the worst case, it iterates through all floors and all spots on each floor).  On average, O(n) if we assume cars are parked quickly.
    *   `unparkVehicle()`: O(m*n) in the worst case (iterates through floors and spots to find the vehicle).  Can be considered O(1) average case.
