**Scalability and Concurrency:**

*   **Concurrency Handling:** The code uses `ReentrantLock` to handle concurrent access to `ParkingSpot` objects. This prevents race conditions when multiple threads try to park or unpark vehicles in the same spot simultaneously. `tryLock()` is used to prevent indefinite blocking, enhancing the responsiveness of the parking lot system. Also, a lock is used to protect concurrent access and modification of the `activeTickets` map.
