You are required to simulate the link navigation of a browser.
The browser should support these two actions:
visit(String url): Visit a new URL. This clears any forward history.
back(): Go back to the previously visited page. If there's no previous page, stay on the current page.
forward(): Go forward to the next page if a back operation was done before. If there's no forward history, stay on the current page.
getCurrentPage(): Return the current URL being viewed.
Input Format:
Implement a class BrowserHistory with the following methods:
public class BrowserHistory {
    public BrowserHistory(String homepage);
    public void visit(String url);
    public String back();
    public String forward();
    public String getCurrentPage();
}
Behavior:
Visiting a new page pushes it onto the history and clears the forward stack.
back() and forward() move the pointer through the history accordingly.
Constraints:
URLs are non-empty lowercase strings.
No more than 10⁴ operations will be performed.
Memory constraints are within reasonable limits for stack-based operations.
Example:
